{
  "texts": [
    "This shift to autoregressive next-scale prediction allowed causal autoregressive models to outperform diffusion models for the first time, while also being significantly faster than both diffusion models and raster-order autoregressive models.",
    "Recent works [20,32] have further improved the speed of VAR, allowing for fast and high-quality image generation.Incorporating text conditions into VAR models is straightforward, as existing text-conditioning techniques from diffusion models can be directly applied in a similar manner.",
    "For example, the cross-attention mechanism used by latent diffusion models [54] for conditional generation can be directly applied to VAR.",
    "Classifier-Free Guidance (CFG) [23] can also be directly applied to VARs [21,59,61]; specifically, just as diffusion models predict and combine scores from conditional and unconditional cases, VARs can likewise predict and combine conditional and unconditional patch classification logits.Despite the improved realism achieved by VAR, text-toimage VARs still lack diversity, often generating similar images when given the same textual prompt (Fig. 1).",
    "This lack of diversity has been observed in other generative models such as diffusion models [55,57] and GANs [38] as well."
  ]
}